         <abstract>
            <p>A conservative difference scheme is presented for the initial-boundary value problem for generalized Zakharov equations. The scheme can be implicit or semiexplicit depending on the choice of a parameter. On the basis of a priori estimates and an inequality about norms, convergence of the difference solution is proved in order O(h&lt;sup&gt;2&lt;/sup&gt; + τ&lt;sup&gt;2&lt;/sup&gt;), which is better than previous results.</p>
          </abstract>
